# Railway → TummlyDb service → Variables
# Name this service "TummlyDb" so the API can reference these values.

# Required. SQL Server rules: 8+ chars with uppercase, lowercase, number, AND symbol.
# Example: !23Tummly.uk  (your current value is missing an uppercase letter)
MSSQL_SA_PASSWORD=12345

# Required so the entrypoint can chown the Railway volume before SQL Server starts.
RAILWAY_RUN_UID=0

# TummlyDb service needs at least 2 GB RAM in Railway → Settings → Resources.

# Volume mount path must be exactly: /var/opt/mssql
# If it still crash-loops after redeploy, delete the volume and create a fresh one.